BeaverTail reads the log file of a Ruby on Rails and displays the entries on a web page.

Steps to install:
  $ cd ~/Sites
  $ git clone git@github.com:tye/beavertail.git
  $ gem install bundle
  $ bundle install
  $ rake db:create
  $ rake db:auto:migrate
  $ rake db:seed
  $ rails s

Login with:
  User: admin@localhost.com
  Password: admin

Misc Features:

  - Controller names and filenames in backtraces use txmt:// links so you can open the files in TextMate
  - When the window loses focus it places a red marker in the list of log entries.

Hotkeys:

Esc       Clears search, collapses all entries and removes focus from the search field
p         Toggles ajax pulling
b         Toggle application/full backtraces
f         Focus search field
h         Hide the currently selected entry
up/down   Move selection up/down list of log entries
right     Expand selected entry
left      Collapse selected entry
tab       Select next entry and expand it
backspace Select previous entry and expand it

